### **SCENE 8: THE CANTEEN CONFRONTATION - LILY CONFRONTS DOXY (25 minutes)**

**INT. WESTVIEW HIGH SCHOOL - CANTEEN - LUNCH TIME**

The canteen is bustling with students. The atmosphere has changed subtly since the assembly - there's a different energy, more awareness, but also tension. Long tables filled with teenagers eating, talking, and navigating the new social landscape.

DOXY sits alone at a corner table, picking at his food. He looks lost in thought, occasionally glancing around the canteen. ETHAN approaches with his lunch tray, clearly nervous but determined.

**ETHAN**
Mind if I sit here? I wanted to talk to you about something.

DOXY looks up, surprised. This wasn't what he expected.

**DOXY**
Uh... sure. I guess.

ETHAN sits down across from him, setting his tray aside.

**ETHAN (CONT'D)**
I know we've had our... issues. And I wanted to tell you something directly.

DOXY sets down his food, paying full attention.

**ETHAN (CONT'D)**
Every time you would call me names, exclude me, or make me feel worthless, it wasn't just a moment for you. For me, it was hours, sometimes days of feeling like I didn't belong anywhere.

DOXY opens his mouth to respond, but ETHAN continues.

**ETHAN (CONT'D)**
I'm not here to make you feel bad. I'm here because I believe you can be better than this. I believe people can change, but they need to understand the impact of their actions first.

DOXY looks genuinely affected, his usual defensive posture softening.

**DOXY**
Ethan, I... I didn't realize it was that bad. I thought it was just normal... I don't know, school stuff.

**ETHAN**
Here's the thing, Doxy. It might have been "normal" to you, but it wasn't normal for me. Every day, I would sit in class wondering if you were going to embarrass me in front of everyone. I would avoid certain hallways just hoping I wouldn't run into you.

The canteen is getting quieter as other students notice the conversation. Some are watching, others are pretending not to listen.

**ETHAN (CONT'D)**
But today, in the assembly, I found my voice. And I want to help you find yours too - but using it to build people up, not tear them down.

DOXY looks around, realizing other students are listening. His instinct is to deflect, but something holds him back.

**DOXY**
(lowly)
I don't know how to fix this, Ethan. I don't know if it's even possible.

LILY approaches the table with her lunch tray.

**LILY**
Can I join this conversation?

Both boys nod. She sits down, positioning herself so she can see both of them.

**LILY (CONT'D)**
The first step to fixing something is understanding the problem. Doxy, what did Ethan's speech mean to you?

DOXY takes a deep breath, clearly struggling with the vulnerability required to answer honestly.

**DOXY**
It made me realize... that I haven't been thinking about other people at all. I've been so focused on making sure nobody thought I was weak, that I became the one who was actually being weak - by picking on people who couldn't fight back.

ETHAN looks surprised by this admission, but also cautiously hopeful.

**DOXY (CONT'D)**
I was wrong. I'm sorry, Ethan. I can't take back what I did, but I want to be better. I want to prove that I can change.

**ETHAN**
I appreciate you saying that. But changing isn't just about saying sorry. It's about doing things differently, day after day.

**DOXY**
I know. And I'm ready to try. I just... I need to learn how.

**LILY**
That's what we're all here for - to help each other learn and grow.

LILY addresses the whole table, but looks directly at DOXY.

**LILY (CONT'D)**
But Doxy, I need to ask you something. Why do you do it? What do you get out of being mean to people?

DOXY considers this carefully, his guards dropping further.

**DOXY**
I... I guess I never really thought about it that way. I just thought that's what you had to do to fit in. To be accepted. To make sure people knew you weren't someone they could push around.

**ETHAN**
What if I told you that people respect kindness much more than cruelty?

**DOXY**
I don't know. I've never tried being kind.

**LILY**
Well, here's your chance. We all make mistakes, Doxy. What matters is what we do after we realize we've made them.

The three sit in comfortable silence for a moment, the canteen gradually returning to its normal volume around them.

**DOXY**
Will you... will you help me? I don't want to mess this up.

**ETHAN**
I will, but you have to really want to change. Not just because you're in trouble, but because you want to be better.

**DOXY**
I do. I really do.

**LILY**
Then we start today. One kind action at a time.

**FADE TO BLACK.**

